1924.description:
Optical Density, OD600, is an indirect measure of biomass density.  A dimensionless quantity.  It's the absorbance of light at a wavelength of 600 nm by a sample of cell culture when compared with a water blank.

For FBA, OD600 is converted into grams of cell dry weight per liter (gCDW/L) by measuring the dry weight of samples of culture of known OD and volume (gCDW/L/OD600).
1924.name: OD600
